## Context
Third stage of the top-level tidy (tracker `0223`). `content/` runs ~7
deliverables through one Quarto project, which forces the exclusion-mask profile
files (`_quarto-manuscript.yml`, `_quarto-manuscript-Gide.yml` — lists of
`!content/…`). Give each deliverable its own folder and its own `_quarto.yml`
so `quarto render deliverables/<x>` selects it directly; the mask files
disappear. Slides are deliverables, not papers, and sit as peers.

## Relevant files
- `docs/repo-layout.md` — target `deliverables/` tree
- `content/*.qmd`, `content/*-vars.yml`, `content/_includes/`, `content/bibliography/`
- `_quarto.yml`, `_quarto-manuscript.yml`, `_quarto-manuscript-Gide.yml`
- `manuscript.mk`, `zoo.mk`, `multilayer-detection.mk` → into each `deliverables/<x>/`

## Actions
1. Create `deliverables/<x>/` per deliverable; move its `.qmd` + `-vars.yml` +
   its `.mk` in. Shared assets → `deliverables/_shared/`
   (bib, `_includes/`, `style-references/`, generated `figures/`).
2. Give each folder a self-contained `_quarto.yml`; reference shared assets by
   relative path (`bibliography: ../_shared/main.bib`) or symlink. Delete the
   three root `_quarto*.yml` mask files.
3. Keep the manuscript's clean-room build discipline: renders from tracked
   handoff artifacts only, no `uv run`, no data fetch.

## Test
- Red first: `quarto render deliverables/data-paper` produces the PDF with no
  reference to the other deliverables (no exclusion mask needed).
- `make manuscript` must not trigger any Phase 1 script or API call.

## Invariants
- Manuscript stays frozen (pinned vars, tracked figures); companions stay live.
- Oeconomia house style preserved for the manuscript.
- No Phase 1 from a writing-side build.

## Exit criteria
- Each deliverable is a self-contained `_quarto.yml` folder under `deliverables/`.
- Root `_quarto*.yml` mask files gone; slides live as peers under `deliverables/`.
- Writing-side build green from handoff artifacts alone.
